                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-02-22</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book was a very smooth reader.  Once you realized that each chapter was based on one of the characters in the book it made the reading more of a visual.  We can all relate to Carmen, intelligent, successful and a smart mouth.  Then there's Asia, who makes you know that you have a real friend in her.  Let's not forget Yani, who we all know is a little naive but has a beautiful spirit.  Hallelujah for Alex and Bryce to help us GAAL's keep hope that there are still good men left.  We all like happy endings, so thank you Shonda for leaving us with a smile and a positive spirit.   It's nice to see our loved ones living happily ever after.  This was a true example of the blessings you may be missing when you continue to live in the past.  Very postive book and I can't wait to read the next one.
<br />
<br /></span>
                  
